Question 1.Question: If the arithmetic mean of 2, 3, 5, 8, Z, 10 and 12 is 7, what is the value of Z?
Question 1.Explanation:
∑x = 2 + 3 + 5 + 8 + Z + 10 + 12 = 40 + Z

Mean = 7 = ∑x/x = (40 + z)/7

7 = (40 + 7)/7

7 x 7 = 40 + Z

49 = 40 + Z

Z = 49 — 40

Z = 9

At equilibrium price, Qd = Qs

30 — 3P = 9P — 18

30 + 18 = 3P + 9P

48 = 12P

P = 4

Put P = 4 into Qd

Qd = 30 — 3(4)

= 30 - 12

Qd = 18

Equilibrium quantity = 18 units
